==English==
===Etymology===
Probably a blend of '''[[fair]]''', '''[[fabulous]]''', and '''[[joyous]]'''

===Adjective===
'''frabjous'''

:A [[nonce word]] in [[w:Lewis Carroll|Lewis Carroll]]'s ''[[w:Jabberwocky|Jabberwocky]]'' 
::'' O '''frabjous''' day! Callooh! Callay! '' &mdash; Lewis Carroll, ''Jabberwocky''

:meaning 
#"very [[joyous]] or [[happy]]"; [[fabulous]]. E.g., a '''''frabjous''''' [[show]], a '''''frabjous''''' [[comedian]].
#"very [[bad]]"; [[outrageous]]; [[terrible]]. E.g., a '''''frabjous''''' [[mistake]].

